comments:
Maintain straight elbow position throughout exercise. Exercise may also be performed with shoulder traveling up to 30º forward, more inline with plane of scapular.

Supraspinatus activity is similar between 'empty can' and 'full can' exercises. However, 'full can' results in less risk of subacromial impingement. Scapular internal rotation and scapular anterior tilt, both of which decrease subacromial space width and increase impingement risk, are greater when performing scaption with shoulder internal rotation (empty can) compared with scaption with external rotation (full can


). (Escamilla 2009)
